data.title: Wellington Phoenix Football Club
data.meta_description: Wellington Phoenix Football Club | Wellington Phoenix is the only professional Football team in New Zealand, competing in the A-Leagues.  | The Wellington Phoenix Football Club is the only professional football team in New Zealand and consists of an A-League Women's team, an A-League Men's team and the Wellington Phoenix Academy which currently caters to three girls youth teams (U20, U17 & U15) and five boys youth teams (U20, U19, U18, U17 & U15)
data.text:
𝗡𝗲𝘄 𝗽𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗻𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽 𝗮𝗻𝗻𝗼𝘂𝗻𝗰𝗲𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 | 𝗪𝗲𝗹𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗴𝘁𝗼𝗻 𝗣𝗵𝗼𝗲𝗻𝗶𝘅 🤝 𝗢𝗣𝗣𝗢 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗘𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗹𝗮𝗿 𝗚𝗿𝗼𝘂𝗽 The Wellington Phoenix are thrilled to announce Entelar Group has joined OPPO as the Wellington Phoenix’s biggest supporters. ‘New Zealand’s total connection company’ will join OPPO as the Phoenix’s front-of-shirt partners for the 2024-25 A-Leagues. Phoenix general manager David Dome said “It’s an exciting time to be involved in football and Entelar Group is an exciting New Zealand company that are ambitious, like us.” We are excited to be launching our 2024/25 season kit with both Entelar Group and OPPO in October! Read more: https://lnkd.in/dWKX-fYZ

Back by popular demand! 🤩 Our Wellington Phoenix Girls Only Experience Camp is back in October! 🙌 Register now to secure your spot! More information and how to register: https://lnkd.in/g9gR7DF4

Grace Jale returns! 🐦🔥 "Now that I've experienced a World Cup and an Olympics I think I'm ready to thrive and take the league by storm" "It's finals at minimum but I'm hoping to win the league with the Phoenix. That's the plan." Welcome back Grace! 💥 See Grace play LIVE from the stands with a Wellington Phoenix A-League women season pass! 🙌 Get yours today: https://lnkd.in/gWA_2vwM #COYN! 🔥 💛🖤 | wellingtonphoenix.com

Yesterday, Wellington Phoenix Football Academy players Daisy Fitchett and Matilda Smith and club mascot Nixie were present at the Queen Margaret College open day! 🙌 Daisy and Matilda were involved in running mini games, while Nixie was interacting with and engaging with different activities at the event! Thank you for having us yesterday QMC!

Phoenix to feature prominently at Wellington Sports Awards The Wellington Phoenix’s achievements over the past year will be celebrated at the Āti Awa Toa Wellington Regional Sports Awards 2024, with the club finalists in five categories: ▪️ Club of the Year - Wellington Phoenix ▪️ Team of the Year - Wellington Phoenix men's first team ▪️ Coach of the Year - Giancarlo Italiano ▪️ Sportsperson of the Year - Alex Paulsen ▪️ Rangatahi sportsperson of the Year - Lukas Kelly-Heald Read more: https://lnkd.in/gujUV4Bp

Phoenix win 'Vibrant Gold' award The Wellington Phoenix were amongst the big winners at The Post Gold Awards for 2024. The Phoenix took out the prize for the Vibrant Gold category which celebrates businesses across the Wellington region in events, hospitality and tourism. Read more: https://lnkd.in/gc25-HsT 📸 - Wellington Phoenix marketing manager Emma Rogers (second from left) and events manager Kya Stewart (second from right) with the Vibrant Gold award.
